<!-- INTRO / CONCEPT -->
<section id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="intro-grid">
      <div class="intro-image">
        <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Janis and Nella in performance" loading="lazy">
        <div class="micro-inset">
          <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Microscope image of bacteria" loading="lazy">
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="intro-text">
        <div class="section-label">01 — The Concept</div>
        <h2><span class="tw-h2" data-tw="Not just human" id="tw-h2-1"></span></h2>
        <p>Recent biology describes the body not as a single organism, but as a living community — human cells alongside bacteria, fungi, viruses and other microbes. This is called a holobiont. There are roughly as many microbial cells in a human body as human ones.</p>
        <p>We became interested in what might shift if we stopped thinking about microbes primarily as things to eliminate. How does it feel to imagine them as part of you — not threats, but long-term cohabitants? That question is where this project started.</p>
        <p>It's also a personal question. In the years after Covid, with hand sanitiser at every door and distance as a social norm, we noticed ourselves becoming more suspicious of contact. I, Holobiont? is partly a response to that — a way of investigating reconnection rather than separation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>



<!-- OUTCOMES -->
<section id="outcomes">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label">02 — Artistic Outcomes</div>
    <h2><span class="tw-h2" data-tw="Three things we are making" id="tw-h2-2"></span></h2>
    <div class="outcomes-grid">
      <div class="outcome-card">
        <div class="outcome-number">01</div>
        <h3>The Lecture Performance</h3>
        <p>A full-evening duet combining dance, live sound design and spoken scientific material. Sometimes funny, sometimes strange. Premieres September 26th, 2026 at Vaasa City Library's Draamasali. Performed in English.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="outcome-card">
        <div class="outcome-number">02</div>
        <h3>Holobiont Jams</h3>
        <p>Participatory sessions — open to anyone — using touch, movement and imagination to explore microbial ideas. We have tried these with different communities during the process and they keep surprising us.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="outcome-card">
        <div class="outcome-number">03</div>
        <h3>The Website</h3>
        <p>An experimental platform launching August 2026 with open-access practices, texts and sound recordings. Continuing what we started with our Metsänalaiset (2022) website — materials for people who can't see the performance, or want to go further.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

