<!-- PROCESS -->
<section id="process">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="process-layout">
      <div class="process-text">
        <div class="section-label">03 — Working Methods</div>
        <h2><span class="tw-h2" data-tw="Research as daily life" id="tw-h2-3"></span></h2>
        <p>Our process includes gut microbiome analyses, fermentation experiments, and homemade bacterial cultures built from cheap aquarium equipment. We read biology papers and movement theory in the same week. We take notes on what it feels like to handle living cultures, not just what the data says.</p>
        <p>We make soundscapes based on quorum sensing — the way bacteria release chemical signals that trigger collective responses in a colony. We find that interesting both as a fact and as a compositional idea.</p>
        <p>A lot of research happens outside the studio. Eating together, taking the bus, walking in the city — these situations kept coming up in our notes, so we stopped pretending they weren't part of the work.</p>
        <p>We also host Holobiont Jams with different communities as we go, partly because it helps us understand what the material actually does when it meets other people, and partly because the feedback is often more useful than our own opinions.</p>
      </div>
